# Context Guide

This directory stores long-lived information that is not visible in code but should guide AI learning, checks, and generated skills. It is not a prompt override directory; built-in task prompts are still maintained by skills-seed.

## Files

- `background.md`: project background, external systems, production facts, rollout or compatibility targets, and manual processes.
- `constraints.md`: long-lived team constraints, forbidden changes, and security, data, release, or operations boundaries.
- `terminology.md`: business terms, aliases, state names, external system names, and code identifier mappings.
- `workspace.md`: cross-project background and coordination constraints in workspace mode.

## Writing Rules

- Put information here only when it should apply to future runs.
- Use `--context` or `--context-path` for one-time learning or sync guidance.
- Do not paste code, long README excerpts, or temporary debugging notes here.
- Empty sections are fine; default placeholder text is filtered out before Agent input.
